It seems to be a conflict between High Sierra and the scikit-image compiler available via pip, so you have to change one of the two.

According to [this post](https://forum.image.sc/t/issues-installing-scikit-image/49085) and some of my other reading, you might have two reasonable options. 

1. Uninstall scikit-image from pip, install from conda-forge:

```
conda activate DLC-CPU
python -m pip uninstall scikit-image
conda install scikit-image -c conda-forge
```

Then try the testcript again.

2. Update your system to macOS Catalina (10.15) or higher.
